<TITLE> Mashrafe likely to miss final Test against WI </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 15 (bdnews24.com) Captain Mashrafe Bin Mortaza is likely to miss the second Test against hosts West Indies as the Bangladesh pace spearhead has yet to recover from a knee injury with two days left before the match. Bangladesh with a 1-0 lead in the two Test series, take on West Indies in the final Test from July 17-21 in Grenada. Mashrafe underwent an MRI scan on Wednesday after injuring his right knee during West Indies' first innings in St Vincent. The scan showed that he had a muscle stress in the knee and not a ligament tear, as feared earlier. A BCB press release said that the report would now be sent to orthopaedic surgeon Dr. David Young in Melbourne, who has treated Mashrafe on previous occasions. The team management will wait for a final word from Young before a decision is taken. However, the type of injury suggests Mashrafe needs a few days rest before bowling. Meanwhile, pace bowler Nazmul Hossain has already reached Grenada as back up for Mashrafe in the second and final Tes
